#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Today‚Äôs lesson is about helping children follow rules and instructions by using consequences.\n"
"\n"
"Consequences are what happen after a child‚Äôs actions ‚Äî good or bad. When children don‚Äôt follow a rule, parents can give a consequence to help them learn.\n"
"\n"
"Clear consequences teach that actions affect others and have results."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "How can calm consequences help you and your family?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Greetings everyone.\n"
"\n"
"Even if you do everything right, your child will misbehave sometimes. We may be tempted to scream and shout, but that just leaves everyone more angry. \n"
"\n"
"If we stay calm, and give them a calm consequence, they will learn to take responsibility for their actions instead."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_father.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_son_5.name,
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Some consequences happen naturally ‚Äî like when a toy breaks, it can‚Äôt be used.\n"
"\n"
"Others you set to help your child follow rules (_‚Äúif you do not pack away your toys, you won‚Äôt be allowed to play with them tomorrow‚Äù_). \n"
"\n"
"Let‚Äôs see how @data.characters.f1_father.name uses consequences to help his nephew, @data.characters.f1_son_5.name, follow instructions:"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_son_5.name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "You are playing so nice and quiet, @data.characters.f1_son_5.name. In 5 minutes, it will be time to clean up your toys."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "*5 minutes later*"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "It‚Äôs time to put away your toys"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No. Not yet!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_son_5.name, should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "@data.characters.f1_son_5.name, either you put away the toys now, or you won‚Äôt be able to play with your toys after dinner."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_father.role_name! should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No @data.characters.f1_father.role_name! I don‚Äôt want to! I‚Äôm not finished with my game."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_son_5.name, should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Because you did not clean up your toys when I asked you to, @data.characters.f1_son_5.name, you cannot play with your toys after dinner. Now please come and wash your hands."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_son_5.name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Good job washing your hands so well, @data.characters.f1_son_5.name."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_father.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Let‚Äôs reflect on how @data.characters.f1_father.name used a consequence here."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_father.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_son_5.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_son_5.name
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"@data.characters.f1_father.name used a consequence to help @data.characters.f1_son_5.name learn that actions have impacts. He did this by:\n"
"- üòå Staying calm \n"
"- üíú Giving a fair consequence related to the behaviour (no playing after dinner if you don't put toys away) \n"
"- ‚≠ê Being consistent by following through with the consequence \n"
"- ü§ùüèæ Involving @data.characters.f1_son_5.name in planning the consequence"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_father.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_son_5.name
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "How does @data.characters.f1_father.name give @data.characters.f1_son_5.name a consequence?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "He makes his disappointment clear"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_father.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Try again! @data.characters.f1_father.name explains the consequence in a calm way."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "He speaks in a calm, firm way, explains why he is giving a consequence, and connects the consequence to the behaviour"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_father.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_son_5.name
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"That‚Äôs right. @data.characters.f1_father.name shows us that it‚Äôs important to introduce consequences when you are feeling calm and makes sure that @data.characters.f1_son_5.name understands why he can‚Äôt play after dinner. \n"
"There are two right answers! Did you find them?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "He gets a bit angry, but then makes the consequence clear"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_father.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Try again! @data.characters.f1_father.name stays calm."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_father.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "@data.characters.f1_father.name follows through with the consequence"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_father.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"That‚Äôs right. @data.characters.f1_father.name shows us that it‚Äôs important to follow-through for the consequence to work. \n"
"There are two right answers! Did you find them?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_son_5.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_father.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_son_5.name
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"What would @data.characters.f1_son_5.name learn if @data.characters.f1_father.name gives in or does not give the consequence? \n"
"\n"
"@data.characters.f1_son_5.name would learn:"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "He can get away with this behaviour in the future"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_father.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Not to take @data.characters.f1_father.name seriously in the future when he gives an instruction"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Exactly. It is really important to follow through with what we say, so our children learn boundaries and know they can trust our word."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_father.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That @data.characters.f1_father.name loves him and forgives him"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_son_5.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_father.name
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Try again! @data.characters.f1_son_5.name would actually learn not to take @data.characters.f1_father.name seriously when he gives an instruction, or that he can get away with this behaviour in the future."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Here are some easy steps to use consequences when your child does not listen."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "BE CALM"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Take some deep breaths or walk away from the situation if you need to.\n"
"\n"
"Then, respond in a calm, clear way."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Shouting at our children only makes things worse. It also teaches them that it is okay to treat others like this when they are upset."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "BE FAIR"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Before giving a consequence, give your child the choice and time to do what you asked.\n"
"\n"
"Give a consequence connected to the behaviour, and make sure it is something you can follow through with."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"For example, if they do not clean up their toys, they cannot play with them the next day (rather than the whole week).\n"
"\n"
"If your child is experiencing a natural consequence for their action already (like not being able to play with their toy after breaking it), you might not need to give them an additional consequence."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "BE CONSISTENT"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Follow through with a consequence every time a rule is broken, even if it feels small. Being consistent shows your child you mean what you say and helps them take the rules seriously."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "If you miss a chance to follow through, do not worry - just try again next time. What matters is keeping it up over time."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "INVOLVE THEM"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Ask your child what a fair consequence might be if a rule is not followed. This helps them learn responsibility and makes it more likely they will stick to the rule."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "More tips"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "You can also involve your child in choosing simple free rewards for when they do follow the rules, to see more positive behaviour!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Now that we have learned a few useful tips, let‚Äôs come up with some ideas for reasonable and realistic consequences."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Would any of these consequences be helpful for you and your child?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "If you are late for dinner, your food will be cold"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "If you continue splashing water out of the bath, bath time will be over"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "If you break your toy, you will have no toy to play with"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "If you can‚Äôt play close to home where I can see you, then you will have to come inside"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Great. Discuss this (or another) consequence with your child and family, and try it out together."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "If you do not put away your toys, then you cannot play with them tomorrow morning"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Great. Discuss this (or another) consequence with your child and family, and try it out tomorrow."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "None of these will work in my home"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That's okay! Try to think of just one consequence that you feel confident you can follow-through with in a calm way. Try starting with something small."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Your home activity is to discuss one household rule that your child finds hard to follow and agree on a fair consequence together. \n"
"\n"
"Remember, if you praise your child when they follow rules, you will see more positive behaviour in your home."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.media_female_13.name's should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Agreeing on consequences together works! Tap play to hear @data.characters.media_female_13.name's story."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @global.app_name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"When my children misbehaved, I would sometimes let it go and other times I would shout at them and punish them right away. But the next time they did it again! \n"
"\n"
"@global.app_name helped me understand that I can do things differently. Instead of punishing them, I stay calm and give them a consequence to help them change their behaviour.   \n"
"\n"
"I have seen a huge change in my child‚Äôs behaviour, and I have less stress. I wish I knew this long ago, but it is never too late to start!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "The next time your child does not follow a rule, can you use a fair consequence in a calm way?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I think so"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That's great! Remember to take a pause before you give the consequence so that you're able to remain calm, and praise yourself afterwards for a job well done!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That's okay. Keep trying. It will get easier in time. You can start by considering smaller behaviours that your child struggles with and planning a fair consequence in advance so you're ready."
msgstr ""
